From 0b8028adf5ec796dae09b18a825291947943e1b7 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Zach Taylor <zctaylor.work@gmail.com>
Date: Wed, 20 May 2026 22:48:46 -0400
Subject: [PATCH 09/48] Add in-process gRPC agent bridge (oh-my-warp)

Routes Warp's agent control ops to a custom gRPC harness host when a gRPC
backend is selected (agent_backends Backend.grpc_endpoint/harness/token).

- Decorator over Arc<dyn AIClient> (server_api/ai/bridge.rs) injected at
  ServerApi::get_ai_client(); the 5 control ops (spawn_agent, send/read/list
  messages, report_event) call the harness host, all other methods forward.
- gRPC client + generated proto types live in an isolated crate
  (crates/warp_agent_grpc: tonic 0.12 + its own prost 0.13) to avoid clashing
  with the app's prost 0.14.
- Phase 3 (live event stream via ServerApi::stream_agent_events) still pending.
